autotools

This program is used to create the boilerplate files and directories
that are needed with a GNU AutoTools based project. These are based on
the following publication, which is included with the distribution as 
ADA553215.pdf.

                   Simple Guide to Using GNU AutoTools
                        ARL-CR-0681 October 2011
                        
                   by Travis Parker and R. Paul Ritchey
                   
This program is modeled after Perl's module-starter with similar
arguments and options. It is designed to boot up a project quickly
and simply with additional modifications to the configuration files as
needed. 

INSTALLATION

To install this program, run the following commands:

	perl Build.PL
	./Build
	./Build test
	./Build install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc AutoTools

